events.description: The release of preliminary estimates for Sweden's annual inflation rate and CPIF for January 2026.

facts.fact_text: Sweden's annual inflation rate rose to 0.4% in January 2026 from 0.3% in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: The annual inflation rate in Sweden rose to 0.4% in January 2026 from 0.3% in the previous month

facts.fact_text: Consumer prices increased by 0.1% on a monthly basis in January.

evidences.evidence_text: On a monthly basis, consumer prices edged up by 0.1% in January

facts.fact_text: The CPI with a fixed interest rate (CPIF) increased by 2% year-on-year in January.

evidences.evidence_text: Meanwhile, the CPI with a fixed interest rate (CPIF), the Riskbank’s target measure, increased by 2% year-on-year in January

claims.claim_text: The January inflation figure was lower than what the market had anticipated.
claims.author: market

evidences.evidence_text: The latest figure came in below market expectations of 0.6%

claims.claim_text: The January inflation reading was the highest since October.

evidences.evidence_text: marked the highest reading since October

claims.claim_text: The CPIF growth was slower than the previous month and missed market forecasts.
claims.author: market

evidences.evidence_text: slightly easing from a 2.1% rise in the previous month and falling short of market forecasts of a 2.1% gain

evidence.evidence_text: the CPI with a fixed interest rate (CPIF), the Riskbank’s target measure
the CPI with a fixed interest rate (CPIF), the Riskbank’s target measure
